text: Artūrs Ņikiforenko (born 1 March 1992) is a Latvian heavyweight judoka and Brazilian Jiu Jitsu (BJJ) competitor. He competed at the 2016 Olympics, where he was eliminated in the first bout. In 2017 he won the European Championship (Brazilian jiu-jitsu). ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Latvian male judoka Category:Olympic judoka of Latvia Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Judoka at the 2015 European Games Category:European Games competitors for Latvia
